'''Yacine Mohamed El Ghazali Titraoui''' ({{langx|ar|ياسين محمد الغزالي تيطراوي}}; born 26 August 2003) is an Algerian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for Belgian club [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]] and the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].<ref name=":0">{{Soccerway|id=yacine-titraoui/760532|accessdate=8 December 2021}}</ref>

== Club career ==
Titraoui made his professional debut for [[Paradou AC]] on 9 August 2021, replacing [[Djaber Kaassis|Kaassis]] in a 2–1 [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1|Ligue Professionnelle 1]] away loss against [[USM Alger]].<ref name=":0" />

On 12 July 2024, Titraoui signed with [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]] in Belgium for three seasons, with an optional fourth.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Charleroi|url=https://www.sporting-charleroi.be/news/yacine-titraoui-est-zebre/|title=Yacine Titraoui est Zèbre !|trans-title=Yacine Titraoui is a Zebra!|date=12 July 2024|access-date=2 August 2024|language=fr}}</ref>

== International career ==
Already an [[Algeria national under-20 football team|under-20 international]] with Algeria, Titraoui was selected to the [[Algeria national football team|senior squad]] by [[Madjid Bougherra]] in November 2021, to take part in the [[FIFA Arab Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tigrine|first=Merzak|date=26 November 2021|title=Coupe arabe des Nations FIFA Algérie/ Madjid Bougherra appelle Yacine Titraoui en renfort|url=https://africafootunited.com/coupe-arabe-des-nations-fifa-algerie-madjid-bougherra-appelle-yacine-titraoui-en-renfort/|access-date=8 December 2021|website=Africa Foot United|language=fr-FR}}{{Dead link|date=December 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Pelard|first=Renaud|date=26 November 2021|title=Coupe Arabe. L'Algérie dévoile ses 23 joueurs sélectionnés|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/equipe-algerie/coupe-arabe-l-algerie-devoile-ses-23-joueurs-selectionnes-e8b4419c-4eca-11ec-a154-8043ea2ede2d|access-date=8 December 2021|website=[[Ouest-France]]}}</ref>

